Interview Questions & Answers (Most Asked)
Q1. How do you check real-time logs in Linux?

A: Using:

tail -f <log-file>
journalctl -f

Q2. What is log rotation?

A: Log rotation automatically compresses, deletes, or rotates old logs to avoid disk full issues.

Configuration: /etc/logrotate.conf

Q3. How do you find errors in logs quickly?

A:

grep -i "error" /var/log/messages
grep -iE "error|fail|critical" logfile

Q4. What is journalctl?

A: It reads systemd logs.

Example:

journalctl -u nginx

Q5. How do you analyze logs of a service?

A:

journalctl -u <service-name> -n 50

Q6. How do you troubleshoot high disk usage due to logs?

A:

Check large logs

Clear old logs

Setup logrotate

Q7. How do you store logs centrally?

A:

ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)

Splunk

Grafana Loki

Fluentd / Fluentbit
